Reneilwe Dhludhlu, Netwerk24Gareth Pahl and Cilliers Naude from Netcare 911 with the girl and her dad. (Netcare911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - A frantic search by police, security officials and paramedics for a "missing and possibly kidnapped" Pretoria toddler has had a happy ending.&nbsp;The 4-year-old Garsfontein girl hadn't actually been missing &ndash; but was just playing hide-and-seek under a table, Netwerk24 reported.According to Netcare 911's Athlenda Mathe, more than 50 people helped look for the child.&nbsp;"The tablecloth moved and Cilliers Naude, of Basic Life Support, looked underneath it. After moving a few chairs, she found the girl," said Mathe.&nbsp;She was lying under the table.Mathe said the girl played hide-and-seek with her father every day when he got home from work, "but this time she'd hidden so well that no one could find her". &nbsp;Her parents had thought she had been kidnapped.Her mom was treated for shock at the scene.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.